    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Py3.11 alpha has been changed to keep only a single exception value internally in `sys.exc_info` instead of a `(type, value, traceback)` tuple. There are a couple of places in Cython where we touch those fields and we should a) adapt and b) make sure we don't unnecessarily swap dead fields in Py3.11.\r\n\r\nIf this stays in CPython until the release, it's probably worth also backporting the necessary changes to 0.29.x.\r\n\r\nFirst reported in https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4499#issuecomment-996251372\r\n\r\nhttps://bugs.python.org/issue45711",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "There's some additional discussion [here](https://github.com/faster-cpython/ideas/issues/106) that indicates that (aside from two undocumented edge cases) the type and tb will always match the value, so Cython could actually just always discard the redundant pointers.",
